cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.DC, cs.IT, cs.SE 

This paper discusses the security and information aspects of Bitcoin and its potential as an exclusively informational money (EXIM). Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of cryptography (cs.CR), computer security and privacy (cs.CY), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), information theory (cs.IT), and software engineering (cs.SE).
